THE TECHNOLOGY TREE
  Education -> Research & Technology -> advanced production

OVERVIEW
  The 'nation' report shows four nation levels:

    Education .... how educated your population is
    Research ..... medical/population research
    Technology ... industrial know-how
    Happiness .... civilian morale

  These levels gate what your sectors can produce and how efficiently
  they do it.  The progression is:

    LCM plants (j) -> libraries (l) -> Education
    Education >= 5  -> tech centers (t) produce Technology
    Education >= 5  -> research labs (r) produce Research

  Happiness and Education have no level requirement and can be
  started immediately.

HOW LEVELS WORK
  Education and Happiness are MOVING AVERAGES.  They represent the
  current state of your population and change gradually.  You cannot
  spike them with a single update.

  Technology and Research ACCUMULATE each update.  They grow as long
  as you produce them, but also DECAY slightly each update:
    decay = level * etu / (100 * age_rate)
  At default age_rate=96 and etu=96: about 1% of your level decays
  per update.  Keep producing to stay ahead of decay.

THE CHAIN: WHAT GOES WHERE
  Step 1 — BUILD LCM (light manufacturing 'j')
    Iron mines (m) -> LCM plants (j) -> light construction materials
    LCM is consumed by libraries, tech centers, research labs, and parks.
    Every sector in the tech tree depends on LCM.  Build LCM plants first.

  Step 2 — BUILD LIBRARIES (l) to raise Education
    Sector:   library/school (l)
    Consumes: 1 LCM per unit produced
    Requires: no level — starts producing immediately
    Education is a slow moving average (window ~480 ETU at 60 ETU/update).
    At 96 ETU/update, education moves about 33% toward its target
    each update.  A single library and 5000 civs raises education
    by roughly 2-8 points in the first update.

  Step 3 — BUILD TECH CENTERS (t) once edu >= 5
    Sector:   technical center (t)
    Consumes: 1 dust + 5 oil + 10 LCM per unit produced
    Requires: education >= 5 to produce anything
    Technology accumulates directly — no averaging.

  Step 3 — BUILD RESEARCH LABS (r) once edu >= 5
    Sector:   research lab (r)
    Consumes: 1 dust + 5 oil + 10 LCM per unit produced (same as tech)
    Requires: education >= 5 to produce anything
    Research accumulates directly — no averaging.

  Step 4 — BUILD PARKS (p) to raise Happiness
    Sector:   park (p)
    Consumes: 1 LCM per unit produced
    Requires: no level — starts producing immediately
    Happiness has a shorter window (~120 ETU at 60 ETU/update) than education.
    See 'info happiness' for why this matters.

PRODUCTION EFFICIENCY (p.e.)
  For sectors that require a nation level, the 'prod' command shows
  a p.e. column.  Production is zero until the threshold is met,
  then scales up gradually:

    p.e. = (level - threshold) / (10 + level - threshold)

  Tech centers and research labs (threshold=5 for education):
    edu=5:   0%     (threshold, nothing produced yet)
    edu=6:   9%
    edu=10:  33%
    edu=15:  50%
    edu=20:  60%
    edu=30:  71%
    edu=50:  82%
    edu=100: 90%
    edu=200: 95%

  Education rises slowly, so expect low p.e. from your tech centers
  and research labs for the first several updates.

WHICH SECTOR PRODUCTION REQUIRES WHAT
  Technology level gates most military production:

    tech >= -10:  food (a), oil (o), lcm (j), hcm (k)
    tech >= 20:   shells (i), guns (d), petrol (%)
    tech >= 40:   radioactive materials (u)

  Use 'show product' to see all thresholds.  The 'prod' command shows
  your current p.e. for every sector — if p.e. is 0%, check your
  tech or education level.

HOW 'PROD' OUTPUT MAPS TO 'NATION' NUMBERS
  The 'prod' command's "make" column shows raw output per update.
  Here is how that raw output becomes the level in your 'nation' report:

  TECHNOLOGY and RESEARCH accumulate directly:
    new_tech = old_tech + raw_tech_output  (before log cap)
    Decay applies each update (~1% at default settings).
    A single tech center producing 3 units/update will raise tech
    by ~3 per update until logarithmic slowdown above tech=1.0
    starts reducing the effective gain.

  EDUCATION is a moving average:
    edu_rate = raw_edu_output * 600000 / (civs * etu)
    new_edu  = (old_edu * edu_avg + edu_rate * etu) / (edu_avg + etu)
    (default edu_avg = 480 at 60 ETU/update; scales with update frequency)

    With 5000 civs, 60 ETU, and one 100% library producing ~25 edu:
      edu_rate = 25 * 600000 / (5000 * 60) = 50.0
      First update from edu=0: new_edu = (0 + 50*60) / (480+60)
                                        = 3000 / 540 = 5.6

    More libraries or more civs shift these numbers proportionally.

  HAPPINESS is similar to education but faster:
    hap_rate = raw_hap_output * hap_edu * 600000 / (civs * etu)
    new_hap  = (old_hap * hap_avg + hap_rate * etu) / (hap_avg + etu)
    (default hap_avg = 120 at 60 ETU/update)

    The hap_edu factor decreases as education rises (educated
    people are harder to please).  See 'info happiness'.

RESOURCE PLANNING
  Key raw material requirements:
    1 library at 100%:     ~1 LCM/avail consumed
    1 tech center at 100%: ~10 LCM + 1 dust + 5 oil per unit
    1 research lab at 100%: same as tech center
    1 park at 100%:        ~1 LCM/avail consumed

  A tech center at edu=10 (33% p.e.) produces ~0.33 tech per avail.
  A tech center at edu=30 (71% p.e.) produces ~0.71 tech per avail.

  Rule of thumb for LCM production:
    Each LCM plant (j) at 100% needs 1 iron per LCM.
    Iron mine -> LCM plant -> libraries/parks/tech centers.
    Early game: 1 iron mine feeding 1 LCM plant feeds ~3-4 libraries.
    Later: tech centers eat 10 LCM per unit — add more LCM plants.

WHAT TO BUILD FIRST
  1. Iron mine (m) + light manufacturing (j) — get LCM flowing
  2. Library (l) — start education; it takes several updates to build up
  3. Once edu >= 5: add tech center (t) and research lab (r)
     You'll need gold mines (g) and oil fields (o) for their inputs
  4. Park (p) — once LCM is flowing; especially once tech > 40
     (see 'info happiness' for when happiness becomes critical)
  5. More LCM plants as tech centers consume 10 LCM per unit

